{
  "text": "Bending energy is a curvature-based method for describing the shape of closed contours, in which the curvature is used to describe or measure the bend state of an object. The bending energy of an object denotes the energy stored in its shape. The more sharply one object bends, the higher curvature it has. Young et al. [CITATION_1] proposed an analysis approach based on the idea of bending energy. In their approach, the bending energy is relying on the total size of the object. The average bending energy per unit length is defined by",
